title: 20th Barking Spider Bash XC
description: The 2016 Spider race features a fun, easy, 9 mile lap course with rolling terrain and terrific spectator viewing.
course:
The course includes the imfamous "Skateboard Park" descent, a twisting, turning tunnel of thrills. There is a new climbing section near the end of the course, so you might want to inspect? This section winds around the front of the old "fill yer pants drop".
Pro/Cat 1/SS--3laps, Cat 2 ---2 laps, Cat 3 --- 3laps
registration: Opens at 8:30 am. Be early, if you don't have your license purchased online already.
notes: Goes off at 11am starting with PRO, Cat 1, SS
directions:
Here are detailed directions to the Spider:
Take 2nd Nampa exit (whether coming from East or West) Go South over freeway to Garriety, turn right go under railroad tracks, then turn left, and then right on 12th Avenue South. Follow SIGNS toward Murphy & Melba out past hospital, 15 miles after leaving Nampa the road will drop down to the Snake River, where you will cross over the bridge BEARING to the left at the "Y" towards Murphy, 3/4 of a mile after crossing river, turn right on Reynolds Creek Road - go 1.5 miles (keep driving thru stinky dairy farm) and event is on the right-hand-side at the Hemingway OHV area.

title: Wednesday Night Eagle MTB Short Track
description: Fast mountain bike racing on a 1.5 mile loop with solid climbing, single track and fast fun descents. Short track racing is a great way to build race fitness and an excellent intro to competitive cycling.
course: 1.5 mile loop with small climbs and descents throughout.
registration:
Pre-register online at Athlete 360.com
Entry fees are $10-Jrs $15 all other categories for pre-registration.
On site registration is $25
notes:
On site Registration Opens - 5:00 pm
Race 1 - 5:30 pm - Cat 1 Jrs, Cat 2 Jrs, Cat 3 Jrs - 20-25 min - $10 pre-registered 
Race 2 - 6:00 pm - Cat 2 Women, Cat 3 Men, Cat 3 Women - 25-30 min - $15 pre-registered
Race 3 - 6:30 pm - Single Speed Men, Cat 2 Men, Single Speed Women, 30-40 min - $15 pre-registered     
Race 4 - 7:10 pm - Elite Men, Cat 1 Men, Elite Women, Cat 1 Women - ~45 min - $15 pre-registered

Various Prizes to be provided from event sponsors

Helmets are mandatory and should be worn at all times while on the bike!

Want to volunteer or have a question? contact Joe Gallegos at jtgallegos0313@gmail.com

Promoted by LBC Inc
directions: From Boise, head west on state street, take a right on old horseshoe bend rd, head north 2 miles and the sports complex will be on the right. Please watch for designated racer parking areas.

title: 2016 Ronde Van Ketchum
course: 3 loop ride including almost all the hills in Warm Springs, North of Ketchum, Sun Valley, and Elkhart
registration: Sign up in person at the Perch or durance before Friday @1300, or online at usacycling.org
notes:
Entry fee includes a 2016 RVK water bottle.

This is a fun ride / tour of almost all of the hills in the north valley.  Pace is moderate.  This is not a race, but a good long ride.

Post event pizza party at the Perch.  Pizza and soda will be available for riders after 14:45
directions:
Start at durance at 0900 sharp.  Look online for the map.
http://www.durance.com/map_Ronde.html

title: Pedal Through the Corners
description: Non-profit, crowd-funded criterium in Meridian, ID. Riders can enter multiple races including a Fixie Crit (onsite registration only), Men 1/2/3, Women 1/2, Men 3/4/5, Masters 40+, Women 3/4.
course: The course is a 0.8 mile loop around the Scentsy Commons facilities. Surface is smooth asphalt with clean corners including one round-about directing riders either direction. The start/finish surface is smooth chip-seal and is a straight-away.  There is plenty of parking to setup your trainer and chairs, as well as a lush green lawn for kids to play.
registration: Registration is free! Well, there's always a catch. USAC will charge a $2.70 service fee, and if you procrastinate and don't register in time, you will pay $35 on site. Register here through USAC.
directions: From the Eagle Rd. freeway exit, drive north on Eagle Rd. Turn left at Pine. Destination is immediately on the left.
